question: Henry places almonds on some baskets. Each basket can hold 36 almonds. If he has 338 almonds and 3 baskets, how many almonds won't he be able to place on the basket?
answer:
Henry will be able to place a total of 36*3 = <<36*3=108>>108 almonds.
Therefore, there are 338 - 108 = <<338-108=230>>230 almonds that he won't be able to place on the basket.
#### 230
